<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1326,970,1676]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,518,1250,1276]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Apterous female</emphasis>
(Allotypus): Body more robust than male, coloration similar to that of male. Connexiva almost joining at level of two last abdominal segments, produced posteriorly into long slender embracing lobes (
<figureCitation box="[811,878,1330,1356]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. A" captionStartId="2.[264,367,1745,1769]" captionTargetBox="[377,1217,608,1718]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[370,1226,603,1726]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. A: habitat of P. horvathi and P. anchicaya in locality Montalvo, La Mayronga (photo F. M. Buzzetti); B: habitat of P. shuar n. sp. in locality Bomboiza (photo P. Tirello); C: P. s h u a r n. sp. female abdomen in dorsal view (photo F. M. Buzzetti); D: P. s h u a r n. sp. male holotype (photo F. M. Buzzetti)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/173726/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number box="[866,878,1330,1356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
